<h3>Queen: A Magnificent Trajectory</h3>
<h2>by Ikumi Obama, Rock Music Magazine vol. 1 1976</h2>
<I>Note: Everything about this comic is bizarre.  It’s a completely fictional spoof on Queen’s origin that appeared in an underground music zine based out of Kansai and is much more cynical and adult-oriented than shoujo manga.  It ostensibly takes place in London, but it’s written as though it takes place in Japan&mdash;Japanese geography, culture, and language are all reflected.  Brian even speaks in Tsugaruben, an obscure, difficult-to-translate northern accent; this gives him a country bumpkin feel although of course in real life Brian is actually extremely intelligent.  Everyone is written way out-of-character.  There is some BL subtext, but it’s not explicit and everyone’s personality is so unrealistic to begin with that I felt like it didn’t really matter.  Freddie in particular has a completely different personality, Roger is an ingenue, and for some reason John was given a stutter.</i>
